  "prompt": "What is formal theory?",
  "response": "Formal theory is a systematic approach to developing and analyzing theoretical models using precise, mathematical language and logical reasoning. Here are key characteristics of formal theory:\n\n1. Core Features:\n- Uses mathematical and logical notation\n- Emphasizes precise definitions and rigorous reasoning\n- Seeks to construct abstract representations of social, scientific, or conceptual phenomena\n\n2. Characteristics:\n- Highly structured and precise\n- Relies on explicit assumptions and axioms\n- Uses symbolic logic and mathematical models\n- Allows for deductive reasoning and hypothesis testing\n\n3. Common Applications:\n- Social sciences\n- Economics\n- Political science\n- Organization theory\n- Decision theory\n- Game theory\n\n4. Key Objectives:\n- Explain complex relationships\n- Generate testable hypotheses\n- Provide predictive frameworks\n- Reduce ambiguity in theoretical explanations\n\n5. Methodological Approach:\n- Develops abstract models\n- Specifies relationships between variables\n- Uses mathematical equations and logical propositions\n- Enables systematic analysis of theoretical claims\n\n6. Advantages:\n- Increases theoretical precision\n- Facilitates comparative analysis\n- Enables more rigorous hypothesis testing\n- Allows for complex system modeling\n\nFormal theory provides a structured, mathematical approach to understanding and explaining complex phenomena across various disciplines.",
